      ImageSizeRaw->{515., 1140.},
      PlotRange->{{0, 515.}, {0, 1140.}}]},
    {
     PaneBox[
      StyleBox["\<\"Figure 4. The Hit/Stand basic-strategy chart produced by \
the package's BasicStrategy function. Rows are player totals (hard on top, \
soft on the bottom), columns are dealer upcards. Red = Hit; green = Stand. \
Doubling and splitting entries of the full chart collapse to H in this \
reduced view \[LongDash] e.g. the player's 11-vs-dealer-6 cell would read \
\\\"D\\\" in a full chart but plays as H here when doubling is not permitted.\
\"\>",
       StripOnInput->False,
       FontFamily->"Helvetica",
       FontSize->10,
       FontSlant->Italic],
      Alignment->Center,
      ImageSize->680]}
   },
   DefaultBaseStyle->"Column",
   GridBoxAlignment->{"Columns" -> {{Center}}},
   GridBoxItemSize->{"Columns" -> {{Automatic}}, "Rows" -> {{Automatic}}},
   GridBoxSpacings->{"Columns" -> {{Automatic}}, "Rows" -> {{0.6}}}],
  "Column"]], "Output",
 CellMargins->{{0, 0}, {10, 14}},
 ShowCellLabel->False,ExpressionUUID->"e8b7d36b-d1ea-4c2e-a443-f68511b0025f"],

Cell["\<\
Two salient patterns in the chart: (a) the player stands on hard 12-16 \
exactly when the dealer upcard is 4, 5, or 6 (the valley in Figure 3); (b) \
soft 18 is a stand against dealer 2-8 but a hit against 9, 10, or A \
\[LongDash] the strong upcards force the player to improve even though 18 is \
\"normally\" enough.\
\>", "Text",ExpressionUUID->"e9f2daf3-59e1-44db-ab9f-2939b3ef38df"],

Cell["5. Monte-Carlo expected value", "Section",ExpressionUUID->"41e83df7-f83e-4983-b427-c77560625a03"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "For any game state the package can estimate ",
 StyleBox["EV(Hit)",
  FontSlant->Italic],
 " and ",
 StyleBox["EV(Stand)",
  FontSlant->Italic],
 " by Monte-Carlo simulation. The unseen-card pool is the remaining deck plus \
the dealer's hole card (since the player doesn't know it); each trial draws \
from this pool, plays the dealer under the current S17/H17 rule, and \
\[LongDash] for Hit \[LongDash] continues the player under basic strategy \
after the mandatory first extra card. The estimator is exposed as"
}], "Text",ExpressionUUID->"fa065ad2-35c9-4217-bf98-39950e3c92e5"],

Cell[BoxData[
 RowBox[{"EstimateEV", "[", 
  RowBox[{"playerHand", ",", " ", "dealerUpcard", ",", " ", 
   RowBox[{"\"\<Hit\>\"", " ", "|", " ", "\"\<Stand\>\""}], ",", " ", 
   "unseenDeck", ",", "\n", "             ", 
   RowBox[{"\"\<HitSoft17\>\"", " ", "->", " ", "False"}], ",", " ", 
   RowBox[{"\"\<Trials\>\"", " ", "->", " ", "600"}]}], "]"}]], "Input",
 ShowCellLabel->False,ExpressionUUID->"be8b4c21-ee6b-4acd-a41c-57e644fc9ef2"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "Rendering ",
 StyleBox["EV(Hit) - EV(Stand)",
  FontSlant->Italic],
 " over the player-total / dealer-upcard grid reproduces the shape of the \
basic-strategy chart as a continuous surface:"
}], "Text",ExpressionUUID->"b2cbdd17-052f-4fbe-aeda-a9a046d3a27d"],

