Cell["6. Card counting", "Section",ExpressionUUID->"9ff629d1-09c9-4837-bac5-ee869803e24c"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "Basic strategy assumes every card in the shoe is equally likely to be the \
next drawn. As a real shoe is played out, that assumption degrades: the \
composition at the bottom of a six-deck shoe can look very different from a \
fresh shuffle. A ",
 StyleBox["card-counting system",
  FontSlant->Italic],
 " tracks a scalar running count that correlates with the player's edge. The \
simplest and most widespread system is ",
 StyleBox["Hi-Lo",
  FontWeight->Bold],
 ", which assigns +1 to low cards (2-6), 0 to neutral cards (7-9), and -1 to \
high cards (10, J, Q, K, A). When many high cards remain, the dealer is more \
likely to bust (Figure 3) and the player is more likely to draw a natural \
\[LongDash] both in the player's favour."
}], "Text",ExpressionUUID->"ef0cac57-448a-4b6a-90d8-6e99d78b6dbd"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "The running count RC is converted to a ",
 StyleBox["true count",
  FontSlant->Italic],
 " TC by dividing by the number of decks remaining in the shoe,"
}], "Text",ExpressionUUID->"6e80d0b8-d540-4223-902e-6779aed169c4"],

Cell[BoxData[
 FormBox[
  RowBox[{"TC", "=", 
   FractionBox["RC", 
    RowBox[{"decks", " ", "remaining"}]]}], 
  TraditionalForm]], "DisplayFormula",
 TextAlignment->Center,
 FontFamily->"Times",ExpressionUUID->"97beb378-496b-4d05-9460-1b2814e046b8"],

Cell["\<\
which normalises the edge signal across different shoe penetrations. The \
player's expected return is close to affine in TC,\
\>", "Text",ExpressionUUID->"ae654b95-2b91-4f59-90ce-e2adb2d1b95a"],

Cell[BoxData[
 FormBox[
  RowBox[{
  "EV", "(", "TC", ")", "\[TildeTilde]", "-", "0.5", "%", "+", "0.5", "%", "\[CenterDot]",
    "TC"}], TraditionalForm]], "DisplayFormula",
 TextAlignment->Center,
 FontFamily->"Times",ExpressionUUID->"4e2e2bb9-ace0-4556-9669-59dc26b5f537"],

Cell["\<\
for typical six-deck rules (the slope ~0.5% per true count is an empirical \
regression coefficient). A classical counting bettor sizes the wager \
proportionally to the edge via the Kelly criterion,\
\>", "Text",ExpressionUUID->"d1de3bb9-35bc-452f-95a6-60ea90907f24"],

Cell[BoxData[
 FormBox[
  RowBox[{
   SubscriptBox["f", "*"], "=", 
   FractionBox["edge", "variance"]}], TraditionalForm]], "DisplayFormula",
 TextAlignment->Center,
 FontFamily->"Times",ExpressionUUID->"fb08fca7-46a8-48d0-a455-a00bcf2ba2db"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "capped at a practical table maximum. The game displays the live running and \
true counts in the ",
 StyleBox["Shoe & card count",
  FontSlant->Italic],
 " opener, and the cumulative bankroll over all rounds in the ",
 StyleBox["Session",
  FontSlant->Italic],
 " plot \[LongDash] so a curious player can watch their edge swing with the \
count over a sufficiently long session."
}], "Text",ExpressionUUID->"19a79222-3220-4c0a-8516-2dc2918bb77b"],

Cell["7. Package architecture", "Section",ExpressionUUID->"2f662a32-7f59-4d1f-a0e0-83cd66dc9650"],

Cell["The code is split into two paclet-style files:", "Text",ExpressionUUID->"a197f303-4bfc-48bf-a70f-8d06bd05fc4f"],

Cell[TextData[{
 StyleBox["Blackjack.wl",
  FontWeight->Bold],
 " \[LongDash] pure game logic, no UI. Exposes ",
 StyleBox["Suits", "Input"],
 ", ",
 StyleBox["Ranks", "Input"],
 ", ",
 StyleBox["MakeCard", "Input"],
 ", ",
 StyleBox["CreateShoe", "Input"],
 ", ",
 StyleBox["DrawCard", "Input"],
 ", ",
 StyleBox["HandScore", "Input"],
 ", ",
 StyleBox["IsSoft", "Input"],
 ", ",
 StyleBox["IsBlackjack", "Input"],
 ", ",
 StyleBox["IsBust", "Input"],
 ", ",
 StyleBox["DealerShouldHit", "Input"],
 ", ",
 StyleBox["PlayDealer", "Input"],
 ", ",
 StyleBox["ResolveRound", "Input"],
 ", ",
 StyleBox["Payout", "Input"],
 ", ",
 StyleBox["CanDouble", "Input"],
 ", ",
 StyleBox["CanSplit", "Input"],
 ", ",
 StyleBox["HiLoValue", "Input"],
 ", ",
 StyleBox["TrueCount", "Input"],
 ", ",
 StyleBox["BasicStrategy", "Input"],
 ", ",
 StyleBox["EstimateEV", "Input"],
 "."
}], "Text",ExpressionUUID->"83615da6-659f-4c67-8d4f-29312f4ba7ce"],

Cell[TextData[{
 StyleBox["BlackjackGame.wl",
  FontWeight->Bold],
 " \[LongDash] the ",
 StyleBox["DynamicModule", "Input"],
 " front-end. Holds all reactive state (deck, multi-hand player, dealer hand, \
bankroll, bet, session history, running count, coach cache), all handlers (",
 StyleBox["doHit", "Input"],
 ", ",
 StyleBox["doStand", "Input"],
 ", ",
 StyleBox["doDouble", "Input"],
 ", ",
 StyleBox["doSplit", "Input"],
 ", ",
 StyleBox["startRound", "Input"],
 ", ",
 StyleBox["advanceHand", "Input"],
 ", ",
 StyleBox["playoutDealerAndSettle", "Input"],
 "), and all widgets (cards, badges, chip buttons, openers, session plot)."
}], "Text",ExpressionUUID->"fd43d360-bded-4bf3-9356-73eabd62b1d7"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "The only non-obvious idiom is that all handler functions are declared in \
the ",
 StyleBox["DynamicModule", "Input"],
 "'s local-variables list. That puts their ",
 StyleBox["DownValues", "Input"],
 " in the same persistent dynamic context as the state symbols they mutate; \
otherwise Button actions silently no-op after the first click because the \
front-end holds stale references to temporary ",
 StyleBox["Module", "Input"],
 " symbols that have been garbage-collected."
}], "Text",ExpressionUUID->"080e1432-580c-4fe7-b62c-3f73bc6c3c95"],

Cell["8. Play the game", "Section",ExpressionUUID->"ab3b6b03-8827-4315-8627-5ed9e55c42e4"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "The notebook loads the two packages from the parent directory of its own \
folder (that is, the directory containing ",
 StyleBox["Blackjack.wl", "Input"],
 " and ",
 StyleBox["BlackjackGame.wl", "Input"],
 "). Evaluate the cell below; a live playable game will appear underneath."
}], "Text",ExpressionUUID->"58a5ace2-ab45-4600-b352-94671148aaf8"],

Cell[BoxData[{
 RowBox[{
  RowBox[{"SetDirectory", "[", 
   RowBox[{"NotebookDirectory", "[", "]"}], "]"}], ";"}], "\n", 
 RowBox[{
  RowBox[{"packDir", " ", "=", " ", 
   RowBox[{"ParentDirectory", "[", 
    RowBox[{"NotebookDirectory", "[", "]"}], "]"}]}], ";"}], "\n", 
 RowBox[{
  RowBox[{"Get", "[", 
   RowBox[{"FileNameJoin", "[", 
    RowBox[{"{", 
     RowBox[{"packDir", ",", " ", "\"\<Blackjack.wl\>\""}], "}"}], "]"}], 
   "]"}], ";"}], "\n", 
 RowBox[{
  RowBox[{"Get", "[", 
   RowBox[{"FileNameJoin", "[", 
    RowBox[{"{", 
     RowBox[{"packDir", ",", " ", "\"\<BlackjackGame.wl\>\""}], "}"}], "]"}], 
   "]"}], ";"}]}], "Input",
 CellLabel->"In[1]:=",ExpressionUUID->"c347de95-26ce-47be-a0c6-8f147f2c5a64"],

Cell[BoxData[
 RowBox[{"BlackjackGame", "[", "]"}]], "Input",
 CellLabel->"In[2]:=",ExpressionUUID->"27ee3328-1648-4320-97cd-71f822ffbf83"],

Cell[TextData[{
 StyleBox["How to play:",
  FontWeight->Bold],
 "\n",
 "\[Bullet] Adjust the bet using the ",
 StyleBox["$5 / $25 / $100",
  FontWeight->Bold],
 " chip buttons, or ",
 StyleBox["Clear",
  FontWeight->Bold],
 " / ",
 StyleBox["All in",
  FontWeight->Bold],
 ".\n",
 "\[Bullet] Click ",
 StyleBox["Deal",
  FontWeight->Bold],
 " (or press N) to start a round. The dealer shows one card; the other is \
face-down until you stand.\n",
 "\[Bullet] On your hand, choose one of:\n",
 "    ",
 StyleBox["Hit (H)",
  FontWeight->Bold],
 " \[LongDash] take another card;\n",
 "    ",
 StyleBox["Stand (S)",
  FontWeight->Bold],
 " \[LongDash] end your turn;\n",
 "    ",
 StyleBox["Double (D)",
  FontWeight->Bold],
 " \[LongDash] available on the first two cards; doubles the bet and deals \
one card;\n",
 "    ",
 StyleBox["Split (P)",
  FontWeight->Bold],
 " \[LongDash] available on any pair of equal-value cards; creates a sister \
hand with an equal bet.\n",
 "\[Bullet] When every hand has stood or busted, the dealer plays and the \
round settles. A natural blackjack pays 3 : 2; any other win pays 1 : 1; push \
returns the bet; bust or loss forfeits the bet.\n",
 "\[Bullet] The ",
 StyleBox["Options",
  FontSlant->Italic],
 " opener lets you toggle H17 / S17, set the number of decks (1 / 2 / 4 / 6 / \
8), adjust the cut-card penetration and the dealer-draw animation speed.\n",
 "\[Bullet] Open ",
 StyleBox["Coach",
  FontSlant->Italic],
 " to see the basic-strategy recommendation and request a Monte-Carlo EV \
estimate for the current state.\n",
 "\[Bullet] Open ",
 StyleBox["Shoe & card count",
  FontSlant->Italic],
 " for the live Hi-Lo running / true count.\n",
 "\[Bullet] Open ",
 StyleBox["Session",
  FontSlant->Italic],
 " for a cumulative bankroll plot."
}], "Text",ExpressionUUID->"55c8c2c3-6186-4bcf-b36e-dde8ffc3bf8e"],

Cell["9. Standalone use (without the notebook)", "Section",ExpressionUUID->"689711fb-7fd2-4a66-8973-068ccddafd78"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "The game runs equally well outside this notebook, in any Wolfram Front End \
that supports ",
 StyleBox["DynamicModule", "Input"],
 ". Clone the repository (or just download the two ",
 StyleBox[".wl", "Input"],
 " files from the ",
 StyleBox["Wolfram/", "Input"],
 " folder) and evaluate:"
}], "Text",ExpressionUUID->"39bb68b6-a49b-41de-a379-b2c189e3b3cf"],

Cell[BoxData[{
 RowBox[{"Get", "[", "\"\</path/to/Blackjack.wl\>\"", "]"}], "\n", 
 RowBox[{"Get", "[", "\"\</path/to/BlackjackGame.wl\>\"", "]"}], "\n", 
 RowBox[{"BlackjackGame", "[", "]"}]}], "Input",
 ShowCellLabel->False,ExpressionUUID->"cbe0351c-afab-42b4-9104-c26ff81568db"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "Or, from a shell (requires ",
 StyleBox["wolframscript", "Input"],
 " and a Wolfram Front End):"
}], "Text",ExpressionUUID->"a96a4ee7-602d-4f28-a64b-b8d975931197"],

Cell[BoxData[
 RowBox[{"wolframscript", " ", "-", 
  RowBox[{
   RowBox[{
    RowBox[{"file", " ", "/", "path"}], "/", "to"}], "/", 
   RowBox[{"BlackjackGame", ".", "wl"}]}]}]], "Program",ExpressionUUID->\
"8cd2d8e2-0f5a-4915-86be-e86ac6c5c4e1"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "which opens a notebook window with the game embedded. The ",
 StyleBox["tests.wls", "Input"],
 " file in the same folder runs a 66-assertion suite covering deck \
construction, ace-aware scoring (including a permutation-invariance \
property), bust/blackjack/soft predicates, S17 and H17 dealer policy, ",
 StyleBox["PlayDealer", "Input"],
 " termination (random trials), round resolution, double/split eligibility, \
payout math, Hi-Lo count, basic-strategy spot checks, and Monte-Carlo EV \
ordering on two known positions."
}], "Text",ExpressionUUID->"d676e591-6d63-404e-b210-b60d9b6890b1"],

Cell["10. References", "Section",ExpressionUUID->"3b1a70cf-0926-4c3d-a499-fe0e1f9f70b0"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "\[Bullet] E. Thorp, ",
 StyleBox["Beat the Dealer",
  FontSlant->Italic],
 ", Vintage, 1966. The original card-counting book; introduced the first \
ten-count system.\n",
 "\[Bullet] R. Baldwin, W. Cantey, H. Maisel & J. McDermott, \"The Optimum \
Strategy in Blackjack\", ",
 StyleBox["Journal of the American Statistical Association",
  FontSlant->Italic],
 " ",
 StyleBox["51",
  FontWeight->Bold],
 "(275), 429-439 (1956). The basic-strategy table, derived by hand at \
Aberdeen Proving Ground.\n",
 "\[Bullet] P. Griffin, ",
 StyleBox["The Theory of Blackjack",
  FontSlant->Italic],
 ", Huntington Press, 6th ed., 1999. The canonical modern reference on rule \
variations and composition-dependent strategy.\n",
 "\[Bullet] J. L. Kelly, \"A New Interpretation of Information Rate\", ",
 StyleBox["Bell System Technical Journal",
  FontSlant->Italic],
 " ",
 StyleBox["35",
  FontWeight->Bold],
 "(4), 917-926 (1956). Optimal betting under a known edge.\n",
 "\[Bullet] Repository (source, tests, math write-up, HTML twin): ",
 ButtonBox["github.com/mthiel74/blackjack",
  BaseStyle->"Hyperlink",
  ButtonData->{
    URL["https://github.com/mthiel74/blackjack"], None}],
 "."
}], "Text",ExpressionUUID->"266c432e-c66e-4865-9307-0368d0c7b327"]
},
Saveable->True,
WindowSize->{1100, 800},
WindowMargins->{{Automatic, 0}, {Automatic, 0}},
